      • getMeasuringTimeStamp

        public long getMeasuringTimeStamp()
        Get the date and time when the transaction was measured. Note that this method is called repeatedly from the same simulated user (re-used).

      • setDefective

        public void setDefective()
        Mark the transaction as defective. This means that a yellow error (of an URL call) did occur between the start and the end of the transaction. The transaction time is still measured but may be invalid.

      • isDefective

        public boolean isDefective()
        Get if the transaction is defective. This means that a yellow error (of an URL call) did occur between the start and the end of the transaction. The transaction time is still measured but may be invalid.
        Returns:
        true if the transaction is defective
